250 g Ground Beef
½ cup Couscous
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
1 tbsp Moroccan Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Honey
113 g Mirepoix
28 g Almonds, sliced
56 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
½ tbsp Oil*

Once boiling, add 1 tsp (2 tsp) chicken stock powder and couscous. Remove from heat and stir to combine.
Cover and let stand for 5 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef and mirepoix. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains and veggies are tender-crisp, 3-4.

Add Moroccan Spice Blend, remaining chicken stock powder and garlic puree. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1-2 min
Add crushed tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened slightly, 2-3 min.
Add honey and spinach. Cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is wilted, 1-2 mins.
Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

When couscous is tender, fluff with a fork.
Stir 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and almonds into the couscous.

Divide couscous between plates.
Top with chorizo tagine.
Sprinkle over feta.

If you've opted to get ground beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the chroizo.